In this article, the White House Press Secretary provides a summary of a call between President Obama and the Director of the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC), Dr. Tom Frieden. The call was about the recently-diagnosed Ebola case in Dallas, Texas. Dr. Frieden informed the President about the strict isolation protocols being used to treat the patient and the ongoing efforts to trace the patient's contacts to prevent further cases. Dr. Frieden also reassured the President that the CDC was prepared for an Ebola case in the US and has the necessary infrastructure to respond effectively.